## Rankings and Reputation  

U.S. News & World Report ranks Holy Cross tied for 27th among liberal arts colleges for 2023, 41st for “Best Undergraduate Teaching,” 89th for “Best Value Schools,” and 59th for “Top Performers on Social Mobility.” [[47](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/U.S._News_%26_World_Report_College_Rankings)]  

* **Money** placed the institution at #5 in its 2022 “Best Liberal Arts Colleges” list. [[48](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Money_(magazine))]  
* **Forbes** ranked Holy Cross 103rd overall among U.S. colleges and 27th among liberal arts schools in its 2025 “America’s Top Colleges” list. [[49](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forbes%27s_College_Rankings)]  
* **Washington Monthly** positioned the college 18th in 2020 based on social‑mobility impact. [[50](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Washington_Monthly)]  
* **Kiplinger’s Personal Finance** listed Holy Cross 15th among the best value private colleges in 2019. [[51](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kiplinger%27s_Personal_Finance)]  
* **PayScale** placed the college 17th nationally for mid‑career salary potential in 2019‑20. [[52](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PayScale)]  

