## Admissions  

Admissions are characterized as “more selective” by U.S. News. [[53](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Selectivity_(admissions))] For the Class of 2028, the admit rate reached a historic low of 17.6%, reflecting the largest applicant pool in the college’s history. [[54](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/College_admissions)]  

* **Standardized Testing** – Holy Cross adopted a test‑optional policy in May 2005; historically, middle‑50% SAT scores ranged from 680–730 (EBRW) and 660–720 (Math), with ACT composites of 29–33. [[55](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SAT_(test))]  
* **GPA** – The average high‑school GPA of admitted students hovers around 3.8. [[56](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grade_point_average)]  
* **Yield Rate** – Approximately 45% of admitted students enroll, a figure that has risen by 13.8% since 2018. [[57](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yield_rate)]  

Tuition for the 2022‑23 academic year was $57,600. [[58](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/College_tuition_and_fees)]  

