## Alumni  

Holy Cross boasts more than 38,000 alumni worldwide, including notable figures in politics, science, arts, and sports:  

* **U.S. Supreme Court Justice Clarence Thomas** – a 1971 graduate. [[66](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clarence_Thomas)]  
* **Dr. Anthony Fauci**, Director of the National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases and chief medical advisor to the President. [[67](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anthony_Fauci)]  
* **Bob Cousy**, 13‑time NBA All‑Star and 1957 NBA MVP. [[68](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bob_Cousy)]  
* **Timothy Leary**, countercultural psychologist and advocate of psychedelic research. [[69](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timothy_Leary)]  
* **Neil Armstrong** (not an alumnus but often confused) – the astronaut corps includes several Holy Cross graduates such as **Joseph P. Kerwin**. [[70](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joseph_P._Kerwin)]  
* **Ann Dowd**, Emmy‑winning actress known for *The Handmaid’s Tale* and *The Leftovers*. [[71](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ann_Dowd)]  
* **Billy Collins**, former Poet Laureate of the United States (2001–2003). [[72](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Billy_Collins)]  

Alumni have also become U.S. Senators, Rhodes Scholars, Marshall Scholars, Truman Scholars, Goldwater Scholars, and winners of Pulitzer, Grammy, Emmy, Tony, and Academy awards. [[73](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_College_of_the_Holy_Cross_alumni)]  

